headline.main: NAZIS CALL PACTS SELL-OUT TO RUSSIA; Radio Resurrects Well-Worn Cry After Hours of Stunned Silence on Moscow Talks

lead_paragraph: LONDON, Nov. 1 -- The German propaganda machine, after four and a half hours of stunned silence, replied to the decisions reached by the United States, Britain and Russia in Moscow with the well-worn Nazi battle cry that Britain and the United States, but more especially the latter, were selling out Europe to Bolshevism.
abstract: BBC broadcasts pact news to Ger pub
